{"key":"processedPost-14495409","value":{"id":14495409,"first":14495135,"last":14495409,"when":1306109909,"utime":"05/23/11 03:18 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>steelmonkey said:</b><br />If the water was at a full boil(thats when you start timing it with your jars in)<br /></blockquote><br /><br />Not correct.<br /><br />You don't start time until steam escapes from under the tight fitting lid.&nbsp; When the water first boils is irrelevant since the jars are not in the water.&nbsp; Depending on how many jars you're sterilizing, steam will begin to escape 5 to 20 minutes after the water starts boiling.<br /><br />When steam escapes, reduce heat to the minimum setting that will keep steam slightly escaping from under the lid. At that point, set timer for 90 minutes.&nbsp; If you feel you'll need to add water, simply have a second small pot of water boiling, so you don't interrupt the steaming cycle if you need to pour some in.<br /><br />You should watch all four <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/BRF-Pf-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">brf tek videos</a>.&nbsp; Everything is demonstrated and explained.<br />RR","title":"Re: Boiling Questions","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}